# Phase 14: Query Advisory Metadata

## Purpose

Produce the analyst-facing advisory layer that the production pipeline doesn't generate. This phase synthesizes technical metadata into actionable query guidance that an AI assistant can use to help analysts write optimal queries.

## Prerequisites

- Phase 1 (Structure Analysis) complete - distribution, indexes
- Phase 3 (Distribution Analysis) complete - distribution strategy
- Phase 9 (Procedure Logic) complete - ETL patterns
- Phase 9B (ETL Orchestration) complete - refresh schedule
- All previous phases provide context

## Analysis Areas

### 1. Distribution & Partitioning Advisory

From Phase 1 and 3 (Synapse), and UC metadata discovery:

```
SYNAPSE DISTRIBUTION ADVISORY:
  Distribution: {HASH(column) / ROUND_ROBIN / REPLICATE}
  Distribution Key: {column or N/A}
  Index: {CLUSTERED COLUMNSTORE / CLUSTERED INDEX / HEAP}

  SYNAPSE PERFORMANCE RULES:
  - {e.g., "Always include PositionID in WHERE or JOIN for data locality"}
  - {e.g., "JOINing two HASH tables on different columns causes data movement -- avoid"}
  - {e.g., "This REPLICATE table is broadcast to all nodes -- JOINs are always local"}

UC (DATABRICKS) ADVISORY:
  Format: {Delta / Parquet}
  Table Type: {MANAGED / EXTERNAL}
  Partitioned By: {col1, col2, col3 / None}

  UC PERFORMANCE RULES:
  - {e.g., "Always filter on partition columns (etr_y, etr_ym, etr_ymd) for partition pruning"}
  - {e.g., "Delta format supports Z-ORDER -- check if additional clustering is applied"}
  - {e.g., "No partition columns -- full table scan on every query; filter by date columns early"}
```

### 2. Recommended Query Patterns

Synthesize from all phases:

```
RECOMMENDED PATTERNS:

Pattern 1: {Common analyst question}
  Approach: {SQL pattern}
  Why: {Explains distribution/index alignment}
  Example:
    SELECT ... FROM {table} WHERE {distribution_col} = @value AND {filter}

Pattern 2: {Another common question}
  Approach: {SQL pattern with JOINs}
  Why: {Explains why this JOIN order is efficient}

ANTI-PATTERNS (avoid these):
  - {e.g., "SELECT * without WHERE -- scans all {N}M rows across all distributions"}
  - {e.g., "GROUP BY on non-distribution column without WHERE -- causes full redistribution"}
```

### 3. Data Freshness Advisory

From Phase 9B:

```
DATA FRESHNESS:
  Refresh Frequency: {Hourly / Daily / Unknown}
  Typical Lag: {N hours behind production}
  Last Known Refresh: {timestamp or "check ETL logs"}
  Stale Data Risk: {LOW / MEDIUM / HIGH}

  ADVISORY:
  - {e.g., "For real-time position data, query production (if access exists)"}
  - {e.g., "Data is refreshed nightly -- intraday positions won't appear until next morning"}
```

